00:09:51,634 --> 00:09:53,288
- Murder?
- Yes, murder.

259
00:09:53,331 --> 00:09:54,898
That's why we're here, sir.

260
00:09:54,942 --> 00:09:56,726
That's why we need to know
where you were this morning.

261
00:09:56,770 --> 00:09:58,249
♪

262
00:09:58,293 --> 00:10:00,425
- I was here at home,
working on my computer,

263
00:10:00,469 --> 00:10:01,862
sending emails.

264
00:10:01,905 --> 00:10:03,733
You could ask my wife
or check my laptop.

265
00:10:03,777 --> 00:10:05,169
- We will.
- I got nothing to hide.

266
00:10:05,213 --> 00:10:08,085
- We will.
Who else has access to the car?

267
00:10:09,043 --> 00:10:11,611
- A kid from the neighborhood,
Devin Williams.

268
00:10:11,654 --> 00:10:13,264
I'm trying to help him out.

269
00:10:13,308 --> 00:10:14,875
He runs errands for us.

270
00:10:14,918 --> 00:10:17,660
I gave him the car last night.

271
00:10:17,704 --> 00:10:18,792
He's a good kid.

272
00:10:18,835 --> 00:10:19,923
He wouldn't do anything
like this.

273
00:10:19,967 --> 00:10:21,969
- Well, did he return the car?

274
00:10:22,665 --> 00:10:24,275
- No, he hasn't.

275
00:10:24,319 --> 00:10:25,668
- Where does he live?

276
00:10:25,712 --> 00:10:27,452
- With his grandma.

277
00:10:27,496 --> 00:10:29,454
Corner of 10th and Bradley.

278
00:10:29,498 --> 00:10:31,152
Tan house.

279
00:10:31,935 --> 00:10:33,589
- All right, thank you.

280
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,112
I apologize.

281
00:10:35,156 --> 00:10:37,419
♪

282
00:10:37,462 --> 00:10:39,508
- What's going on with you?
What the hell was that?

283
00:10:39,551 --> 00:10:40,944
- Kid had a black eye.

284
00:10:40,988 --> 00:10:42,816
- Yeah, it sounds like she got
it at soccer practice.

285
00:10:42,859 --> 00:10:44,600
You kept pushing.
We're chasing a murder here.

286
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:45,949
- I don't care
what we're chasing.

287
00:10:45,993 --> 00:10:47,298
She's a kid.
She needs to be protected.

288
00:10:47,342 --> 00:10:48,691
- That is not the point.

289
00:10:48,735 --> 00:10:50,040
- I asked a simple question.
It's not a big deal.

290
00:10:50,084 --> 00:10:52,129
- Hailey, look,
you outrank me in everything,

291
00:10:52,173 --> 00:10:53,478
but if you're gonna
accuse a father

292
00:10:53,522 --> 00:10:54,828
of smacking around his kid,

293
00:10:54,871 --> 00:10:56,481
you gotta have
some evidence first.

294
00:10:56,525 --> 00:10:58,658
- I did.
It's called a black eye.

295
00:10:58,701 --> 00:11:00,268
♪

296
00:11:00,311 --> 00:11:01,791
Don't ever undermine me
or dismiss me

297
00:11:01,835 --> 00:11:03,401
from an interview
like that again.

298
00:11:03,445 --> 00:11:09,581
♪

299
00:11:09,625 --> 00:11:12,846
[train roaring]

300
00:11:13,716 --> 00:11:16,676
[suspenseful music]

301
00:11:16,719 --> 00:11:23,944
♪

302
00:11:26,207 --> 00:11:28,383
- Hold up.

303
00:11:35,564 --> 00:11:37,348
Bingo.
Blue Honda inside.

304
00:11:37,392 --> 00:11:39,350
- All right, come on.

305
00:11:47,794 --> 00:11:50,057
Hello, ma'am.
Chicago PD.

306
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:52,407
Is Devin Williams home?
We'd like to talk to him.

307
00:11:52,450 --> 00:11:53,756
- What's this about?

308
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,018
Why y'all want to talk to him?

309
00:11:55,062 --> 00:11:56,716
- The car he was driving
was spotted

310
00:11:56,759 --> 00:11:58,021
near the scene of a murder.

311
00:11:58,065 --> 00:11:59,240
- Murder?

312
00:11:59,283 --> 00:12:00,545
Devin ain't involved in
no damn murder.

313
00:12:00,589 --> 00:12:02,199
I can promise you that much.

314
00:12:02,243 --> 00:12:03,723
- Yeah well, that's great.
Then we'll be in and out.

315
00:12:03,766 --> 00:12:06,116
Two, three minutes.

316
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:08,466
- The truth is, ma'am, is that

317
00:12:08,510 --> 00:12:10,033
we know Devin isn't involved.

318
00:12:10,077 --> 00:12:11,643
We've heard really good things
about him.

319
00:12:11,687 --> 00:12:14,734
But, you know, we gotta
check him off a list, so...

320
00:12:21,262 --> 00:12:22,567
- Come on in.

321
00:12:22,611 --> 00:12:24,221
Devin!

322
00:12:24,265 --> 00:12:25,919
Can I get you all something
to drink?

323
00:12:25,962 --> 00:12:28,443
Some water, some tea,
some coffee, or something?

324
00:12:29,444 --> 00:12:31,402
Wait a--wait a minute!
- He's running your way.

325
00:12:31,446 --> 00:12:33,056
- Devin, don't run.
Boy, get back here.

326
00:12:33,100 --> 00:12:35,015
- Stop right there.
Stop, man. Stop!

327
00:12:35,058 --> 00:12:37,191
Stop, stop!
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

328
00:12:37,234 --> 00:12:38,975
- Stay down.
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

329
00:12:39,019 --> 00:12:40,324
You're done, bro. You're done.
You're done. You're done.

330
00:12:40,368 --> 00:12:41,412
Stay down.

331
00:12:41,456 --> 00:12:43,066
- You're under arrest
for murder.

332
00:12:43,110 --> 00:12:44,372
- No. No, no, no, no.
You got the wrong guy.

333
00:12:44,415 --> 00:12:46,113
I got nothing to do
with that murder

334
00:12:46,156 --> 00:12:47,810
on the North Side, I swear.
You got the wrong guy!

335
00:12:47,854 --> 00:12:49,377
- Murder on the North Side?
What you talking about, pal?

336
00:12:49,420 --> 00:12:50,900
- The one where
that lady got killed.

337
00:12:50,944 --> 00:12:52,380
I--I didn't--I didn't do that,
I swear.

338
00:12:52,423 --> 00:12:55,513
- Okay, we believe you, Devin.
We really do.

339
00:12:55,557 --> 00:12:57,341
- Come on.

340
00:13:00,910 --> 00:13:01,128
.

341
00:13:01,171 --> 00:13:03,521
- The best thing you can do
is tell us

342
00:13:03,565 --> 00:13:04,827
what really happened
at that house.

343
00:13:04,871 --> 00:13:06,611
If you do that, we can talk to

344
00:13:06,655 --> 00:13:08,091
the State's Attorney's Office
and try to work out

345
00:13:08,135 --> 00:13:10,311
a good deal.

346
00:13:10,354 --> 00:13:12,748
- Like I said,
I didn't kill her.

347
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:15,838
I haven't been to
the North Side in...weeks.

348
00:13:15,882 --> 00:13:17,666
- Okay.
The problem is, Devin,

349
00:13:17,709 --> 00:13:19,973
you keep talking about a murder
on the North Side...

350
00:13:20,016 --> 00:13:21,409
Right?
- Mm-hmm.

351
00:13:21,452 --> 00:13:23,846
- We never told you about that.

352
00:13:23,890 --> 00:13:26,153
- What do you mean?
- You keep denying something

353
00:13:26,196 --> 00:13:27,328
you shouldn't know about.

354
00:13:27,371 --> 00:13:30,897
Means you're guilty.

355
00:13:30,940 --> 00:13:33,073
- But I'm not.

356
00:13:33,116 --> 00:13:34,335
- Then how do you know someone

357
00:13:34,378 --> 00:13:35,945
from the North Side was
murdered?

358
00:13:37,381 --> 00:13:39,862
- I...

359
00:13:39,906 --> 00:13:42,865
just know...I guess.

360
00:13:42,909 --> 00:13:45,737
- Where were you this morning
between 9:00 and 10:00?

361
00:13:45,781 --> 00:13:49,045
- Humboldt Park.
Uh, I was, uh, smoking weed

362
00:13:49,089 --> 00:13:50,699
near the chess tables.

363
00:13:50,742 --> 00:13:54,007
- Hey, look at me.
You still high?

364
00:13:54,050 --> 00:13:56,096
- Yeah, but only a little.

365
00:13:56,139 --> 00:13:58,533
- Yeah. Were you alone,
with someone else?

366
00:13:58,576 --> 00:14:00,404
- I was with someone else.
- Who?

367
00:14:00,448 --> 00:14:03,799
- God.

368
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:05,279
- God?

369
00:14:05,322 --> 00:14:07,542
- Yeah.
We were hanging out.

370
00:14:07,585 --> 00:14:10,110
Talking to each other.

371
00:14:10,153 --> 00:14:11,894
And it was really nice.

372
00:14:11,938 --> 00:14:14,897
[tense music]

373
00:14:14,941 --> 00:14:16,029
♪

374
00:14:16,072 --> 00:14:18,248
- Is this guy bluffing?

375
00:14:18,292 --> 00:14:20,294
Or is he really that clueless?

376
00:14:21,164 --> 00:14:22,687
- I just talked to the lab.
- Yeah?

377
00:14:22,731 --> 00:14:24,776
- Still no fingerprints
or DNA hits.

378
00:14:24,820 --> 00:14:26,778
- We got the witness, though,
Sarge.

379
00:14:26,822 --> 00:14:28,345
Neighbor said she got
a good look at the offender.

380
00:14:28,389 --> 00:14:29,564
- That's right.

381
00:14:29,607 --> 00:14:31,131
Well, get her down here
right away.

382
00:14:38,573 --> 00:14:40,227
Just let us know if you see
the man you saw

383
00:14:40,270 --> 00:14:42,533
standing outside of Allison's
house this morning.

384
00:14:42,577 --> 00:14:45,188
Take a look.
See if anyone looks familiar.

385
00:14:45,232 --> 00:14:52,456
♪

386
00:14:54,632 --> 00:14:56,460
- I'm pretty sure
it's number three.

387
00:14:59,115 --> 00:15:00,334
- Good.
Thank you.

388
00:15:00,377 --> 00:15:02,902
- Why don't we step outside?

389
00:15:07,819 --> 00:15:09,125
- I guess we got him, boss.

390
00:15:09,169 --> 00:15:11,432
- Yeah, all right.
So, take a run at him.

391
00:15:11,475 --> 00:15:14,043
Let's put this thing to bed.

392
00:15:14,087 --> 00:15:15,523
- Copy that.

393
00:15:15,566 --> 00:15:18,308
♪

394
00:15:18,352 --> 00:15:20,006
'Sup, bro?
- 'Sup?

395
00:15:20,049 --> 00:15:21,746
- Oh, let me
help you out with those.

396
00:15:21,790 --> 00:15:23,052
- Oh, thanks.
- Hey, bro, hold on.

397
00:15:23,096 --> 00:15:25,054
Let me help you with these.
- Okay.

398
00:15:25,098 --> 00:15:27,274
- You want a sandwich or
something to go with those?

399
00:15:27,317 --> 00:15:29,319
Just let me know.
- Yeah, that would be awesome.

400
00:15:29,363 --> 00:15:31,974
- Yeah, man.

401
00:15:32,018 --> 00:15:34,585
First thing's first.
Let's talk about what happened.

402
00:15:34,629 --> 00:15:35,978
- Cool.

403
00:15:36,022 --> 00:15:37,284
- I'm gonna keep it 100
with you, man.

404
00:15:37,327 --> 00:15:38,633
No BS, no games.

405
00:15:38,676 --> 00:15:40,852
- I appreciate that.

406
00:15:42,158 --> 00:15:45,814
- A witness just...
picked you out of a lineup.

407
00:15:45,857 --> 00:15:47,990
She said she saw you
outside the house

408
00:15:48,034 --> 00:15:50,471
the morning of the murder.
We also got that getaway car,

409
00:15:50,514 --> 00:15:53,909
the blue Honda--found that
parked at your granny's garage.

410
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:56,042
This is where it gets bad.

411
00:15:56,085 --> 00:15:58,305
Your fingerprints are
all over the crowbar

412
00:15:58,348 --> 00:16:01,525
that killed the female victim.

413
00:16:01,569 --> 00:16:03,658
We know you did the murder.

414
00:16:03,701 --> 00:16:06,661
But I think you're
a decent kid,

415
00:16:06,704 --> 00:16:09,577
and I would love
to give you a deal.

416
00:16:09,620 --> 00:16:11,318
I just need you
to help me understand

417
00:16:11,361 --> 00:16:14,625
what really happened.

418
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:18,151
- I keep trying to tell
you guys, I didn't kill her.

419
00:16:18,194 --> 00:16:20,936
I was in Humboldt Park.

420
00:16:23,721 --> 00:16:26,550
Can I get one of them
sandwiches now?

421
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:39,128
- How's that sandwich?

422
00:16:40,608 --> 00:16:43,045
Yeah, well, I were you,
I'd enjoy it.

423
00:16:44,742 --> 00:16:47,136
'Cause the food
in prison sucks.

424
00:16:48,877 --> 00:16:50,139
Well, I guess you
already know that.

425
00:16:50,183 --> 00:16:52,794
You did two years
in Danville, right?

426
00:16:54,187 --> 00:16:56,058
Well, honey...

427
00:16:56,102 --> 00:16:58,191
I'm here to tell you,
life is different.

428
00:16:59,844 --> 00:17:02,325
There's no light
at the end of the tunnel.

429
00:17:02,369 --> 00:17:04,849
There's no calendar.

430
00:17:05,850 --> 00:17:07,374
No girlfriend
to look forward to.

431
00:17:07,417 --> 00:17:09,245
It's just you.

432
00:17:09,289 --> 00:17:11,552
And your cell.

433
00:17:11,595 --> 00:17:13,815
Forever.

434
00:17:17,732 --> 00:17:19,995
That's why we're trying
to help you, Devin.

435
00:17:20,039 --> 00:17:22,998
To give you that light
at the end of the tunnel.

436
00:17:24,260 --> 00:17:26,219
- I'm really thirsty.
Can--can I get another soda?

437
00:17:26,262 --> 00:17:28,047
[loud bang]

438
00:17:28,699 --> 00:17:30,179
- You think I'm running
a restaurant?

439
00:17:30,223 --> 00:17:31,659
- No, I'm--I'm just
really thirsty.

440
00:17:31,702 --> 00:17:33,530
- We got a young woman
beaten to death,

441
00:17:33,574 --> 00:17:36,316
and all you care about is pop?

442
00:17:38,274 --> 00:17:40,320
- I'm sorry, sir.
I--I don't mean no disrespect.

443
00:17:40,363 --> 00:17:41,538
- Let me tell you something,

444
00:17:41,582 --> 00:17:43,758
that woman you killed?

445
00:17:43,801 --> 00:17:46,195
Her husband is an alderman.

446
00:17:46,239 --> 00:17:48,719
And that's about as close
as you get

447
00:17:48,763 --> 00:17:51,026
to being a king in Chicago.

448
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:54,551
And when the wife
of an alderman

449
00:17:54,595 --> 00:17:57,772
gets beaten to death
with a crowbar,

450
00:17:57,815 --> 00:18:00,601
somebody is gonna pay.

451
00:18:00,644 --> 00:18:02,907
You understand?

452
00:18:02,951 --> 00:18:06,389
The only question is,
how much?

453
00:18:06,433 --> 00:18:09,392
How long?
How painful?

454
00:18:09,436 --> 00:18:15,442
♪

455
00:18:15,485 --> 00:18:17,661
- I keep telling you guys,
I didn't do it.

456
00:18:17,705 --> 00:18:20,099
I--I was in Humboldt Park.

457
00:18:22,971 --> 00:18:25,756
Now, if it's okay, can I--can I
please get that soda?

458
00:18:33,895 --> 00:18:34,243
.

459
00:18:34,287 --> 00:18:36,202
- Kid is a trip.
- Yup.

460
00:18:36,245 --> 00:18:37,725
- Can't figure out where
he's coming from.

461
00:18:37,768 --> 00:18:39,509
- No, well, whatever he's
doing, it's working.

462
00:18:39,553 --> 00:18:41,163
It's been seven hours; he
hasn't given up a damn thing.

463
00:18:41,207 --> 00:18:42,556
- Yeah, he hasn't
lawyered up yet, though,

464
00:18:42,599 --> 00:18:44,166
which is good, but it's odd.

465
00:18:44,210 --> 00:18:46,081
I mean, I don't know why he's
still talking to us.

466
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,604
- He doesn't know any better.

467
00:18:47,648 --> 00:18:49,345
- Lab says there's still
no forensics

468
00:18:49,389 --> 00:18:51,260
tying Devin to the crowbar
and body,

469
00:18:51,304 --> 00:18:52,653
the crime scene--nothing.

470
00:18:52,696 --> 00:18:54,437
- Sarge, let me take
a run at him.

471
00:18:54,481 --> 00:18:55,917
I've been going over his file.
I think I have

472
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:57,223
an angle to play.

473
00:18:57,266 --> 00:18:59,747
- Give it a shot.
Oh--

474
00:18:59,790 --> 00:19:01,531
Kid wants a pop.

475
00:19:01,575 --> 00:19:04,882
- Ah.

476
00:19:12,412 --> 00:19:15,110
I just wanted to check in
on you.

477
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:17,417
See how you're holding up.

478
00:19:22,422 --> 00:19:24,685
Is it okay if I sit down?

479
00:19:39,656 --> 00:19:42,311
How old were you
when they started?

480
00:19:44,879 --> 00:19:47,098
- When what started?

481
00:19:47,142 --> 00:19:49,492
- The beatings.

482
00:19:55,281 --> 00:19:58,240
- I don't know.

483
00:19:58,284 --> 00:20:00,242
Five.

484
00:20:00,286 --> 00:20:02,853
Six.

485
00:20:03,898 --> 00:20:06,640
- Your dad, he beat
your mom, too, right?

486
00:20:07,815 --> 00:20:10,252
- Yeah.

487
00:20:10,296 --> 00:20:12,776
That's why I had to move.

488
00:20:21,437 --> 00:20:23,918
- When was it the worst?

489
00:20:23,961 --> 00:20:26,050
Morning?

490
00:20:26,094 --> 00:20:28,052
Night?

491
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:37,018
For me, it was worst
on the weekends.

492
00:20:39,107 --> 00:20:41,196
My dad...

493
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,284
[tense music]

494
00:20:42,328 --> 00:20:44,243
Would start drinking early.

495
00:20:44,286 --> 00:20:47,071
Like, noon.

496
00:20:47,115 --> 00:20:49,291
He'd just sit around...

497
00:20:49,335 --> 00:20:51,685
getting more and more
pissed off.

498
00:20:51,728 --> 00:20:55,515
My brothers and I,
we were just kids, you know?

499
00:20:55,558 --> 00:20:57,517
We wanted to have fun.

500
00:20:57,560 --> 00:20:59,606
♪

501
00:20:59,649 --> 00:21:01,869
And it drove him crazy.

502
00:21:03,871 --> 00:21:07,309
So he'd pick a fight
with my mom,

503
00:21:07,353 --> 00:21:09,398
saying that we were
being too loud.

504
00:21:10,486 --> 00:21:14,751
She'd defend us,
because she always did.

505
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:20,801
So he'd go after her.

506
00:21:23,717 --> 00:21:26,937
And then he'd come after us...

507
00:21:26,981 --> 00:21:29,679
with anything he could get
his hands on.

508
00:21:29,723 --> 00:21:33,944
Belt...
extension cord.

509
00:21:37,034 --> 00:21:39,254
- You ever think
about killing yourself?

510
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:45,913
♪

511
00:21:45,956 --> 00:21:48,307
- Yeah.

512
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:52,398
But I didn't,
because I'm strong like you.

513
00:21:54,095 --> 00:21:55,879
- Hailey's good.

514
00:21:55,923 --> 00:21:57,359
This cop thing
doesn't work out,

515
00:21:57,403 --> 00:22:00,406
she should think
about being an actor.

516
00:22:00,449 --> 00:22:02,059
Damn.

