00:33:37,189 --> 00:33:38,755
- All right, so he did know

773
00:33:38,799 --> 00:33:40,453
it was his wife's watch--that
means he was lying to us.

774
00:33:40,496 --> 00:33:42,542
- He also made two $9,000
withdrawals

775
00:33:42,585 --> 00:33:45,806
while his bro, Nate, made two
$9,000 deposits last week.

776
00:33:45,849 --> 00:33:47,851
- All right, so Collier paid
Nate 18 grand

777
00:33:47,895 --> 00:33:51,116
to whack his wife, and he
whacked Nate to tie things off.

778
00:33:51,159 --> 00:33:53,074
The question is, why?

779
00:33:53,118 --> 00:33:54,684
- I think I have the answer
to that.

780
00:33:54,728 --> 00:33:56,556
Found an email Allison wrote
to one of her friends.

781
00:33:56,599 --> 00:33:58,340
"Need to talk to you about
finding a good lawyer.

782
00:33:58,384 --> 00:34:00,386
Lots to discuss.
None of it good."

783
00:34:05,130 --> 00:34:09,003
- She seemed pretty desperate
to begin the process,

784
00:34:09,047 --> 00:34:11,875
so I gave her the name of a few
divorce lawyers that I know.

785
00:34:11,919 --> 00:34:14,182
- Okay, did she mention why
she wanted to split up?

786
00:34:14,226 --> 00:34:17,272
- Yes.
But given what's happened,

787
00:34:17,316 --> 00:34:19,666
there's probably no point
in talking about it.

788
00:34:19,709 --> 00:34:21,189
- Well, there's
definitely a point.

789
00:34:21,233 --> 00:34:22,495
- What do you mean?

790
00:34:22,538 --> 00:34:24,366
- We think her husband's
involved.

791
00:34:24,410 --> 00:34:29,067
♪

792
00:34:29,110 --> 00:34:31,721
- Oh, my God.

793
00:34:31,765 --> 00:34:34,898
It was Jason.
It all makes perfect sense.

794
00:34:34,942 --> 00:34:36,378
- How?

795
00:34:36,422 --> 00:34:38,902
- Jason Collier was
physically abusing Allison,

796
00:34:38,946 --> 00:34:41,905
and she wanted a divorce.

797
00:34:41,949 --> 00:34:43,733
So he had her killed.

798
00:34:44,995 --> 00:34:46,693
- You're sure about this?

799
00:34:46,736 --> 00:34:48,477
- Afraid so.

800
00:34:48,521 --> 00:34:50,262
- Is he in custody?

801
00:34:50,305 --> 00:34:52,307
- I went by his office,
his house...

802
00:34:52,351 --> 00:34:53,961
He's in the wind.

803
00:34:54,004 --> 00:34:55,441
- Let me reach out to him.

804
00:34:55,484 --> 00:34:57,573
I'll tell him the person we
think is responsible

805
00:34:57,617 --> 00:35:00,881
for Allison's death,
this Nate Stevenson guy,

806
00:35:00,924 --> 00:35:02,665
was just found dead.

807
00:35:02,709 --> 00:35:04,798
The case is officially closed.

808
00:35:06,060 --> 00:35:08,106
- Let me know when and where.

809
00:35:08,802 --> 00:35:12,545
- I had no idea
Jason was capable of this.

810
00:35:14,503 --> 00:35:16,679
- Everyone is capable of this.

811
00:35:16,723 --> 00:35:19,987
It's why we're so busy.

812
00:35:31,433 --> 00:35:32,869
- I know you don't wanna
talk about it.

813
00:35:32,913 --> 00:35:36,438
- That's a terrible way to
start a sentence.

814
00:35:36,482 --> 00:35:38,788
- I wanna make sure
you're okay.

815
00:35:40,529 --> 00:35:43,750
- I can't believe
he killed himself.

816
00:35:43,793 --> 00:35:45,969
- I know.
I get it.

817
00:35:46,013 --> 00:35:49,451
- Internal Affairs wants
to look into it now.

818
00:35:49,495 --> 00:35:52,802
Apparently, they have concerns
about my interrogation tactics.

819
00:35:52,846 --> 00:35:54,978
- Screw that.
You did it right.

820
00:35:55,022 --> 00:35:57,329
- Maybe.
- No, definitely.

821
00:35:59,200 --> 00:36:01,768
- There he is.

822
00:36:01,811 --> 00:36:03,378
- Collier's on site.
He's heading east on

823
00:36:03,422 --> 00:36:04,858
Randolph, toward his house.

824
00:36:07,252 --> 00:36:10,211
[suspenseful music]

825
00:36:10,255 --> 00:36:17,000
♪

826
00:36:17,044 --> 00:36:19,046
- Take him.

827
00:36:24,443 --> 00:36:27,707
[motor revving]

828
00:36:37,891 --> 00:36:40,633
- Go to the next block.
I got the alley.

829
00:36:43,375 --> 00:36:50,251
♪

830
00:36:50,295 --> 00:36:51,905
He's going through the yards.

831
00:36:57,215 --> 00:36:58,651
Stop running!

832
00:36:58,694 --> 00:37:00,957
Stop--police!
Stop running!

833
00:37:10,315 --> 00:37:12,273
Chicago PD!
Don't move.

834
00:37:12,317 --> 00:37:14,667
Get your hands in the air now!

835
00:37:14,710 --> 00:37:17,539
Jason Collier,
you're under arrest for murder.

836
00:37:17,583 --> 00:37:19,367
Hands in the air now.

837
00:37:19,411 --> 00:37:22,892
- This whole damn thing
is her fault.

838
00:37:22,936 --> 00:37:25,155
She made a big deal
over nothing.

839
00:37:26,766 --> 00:37:27,723
Nothing!

840
00:37:27,767 --> 00:37:29,551
I grabbed her arms a few times.

841
00:37:29,595 --> 00:37:32,728
That doesn't mean she gets
to ruin my career.

842
00:37:32,772 --> 00:37:33,729
My life.

843
00:37:33,773 --> 00:37:36,079
- Get on your knees now.

844
00:37:36,123 --> 00:37:38,430
- Screw that.

845
00:37:39,953 --> 00:37:42,738
- Stay back.
Stay back!

846
00:37:45,001 --> 00:37:47,874
Drop your weapon.
I will shoot you.

847
00:37:49,179 --> 00:37:51,399
Drop your weapon!

848
00:37:51,443 --> 00:37:53,009
Drop your weapon now!

849
00:37:54,446 --> 00:37:55,882
I will shoot you!

850
00:37:55,925 --> 00:37:57,971
Drop your weapon.
I'll--

851
00:38:06,109 --> 00:38:09,199
- [groaning]

852
00:38:18,818 --> 00:38:21,081
- I ordered the suspect
to get on his knees.

853
00:38:21,124 --> 00:38:22,604
He refused to comply.

854
00:38:22,648 --> 00:38:23,779
And then he reached
into his waistband

855
00:38:23,823 --> 00:38:25,390
and pulled out a weapon.

856
00:38:25,433 --> 00:38:27,609
- But you didn't engage.

857
00:38:27,653 --> 00:38:30,351
- No.
- Okay, why not?

858
00:38:30,395 --> 00:38:31,657
- I shot before she could,
boss.

859
00:38:31,700 --> 00:38:34,181
- Well, I know that, Adam.

860
00:38:34,224 --> 00:38:36,575
I'm trying to understand
why Hailey didn't fire

861
00:38:36,618 --> 00:38:38,707
on the offender before you did.

862
00:38:38,751 --> 00:38:40,796
- She had two pedestrians
in her line of fire.

863
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,537
She knew I was there.
She knew I had the shot,

864
00:38:42,581 --> 00:38:44,365
so she let me take it.

865
00:38:44,409 --> 00:38:47,368
- Is that what happened?

866
00:38:47,412 --> 00:38:50,110
- Yeah.

867
00:38:51,677 --> 00:38:55,028
- Okay, good.

868
00:38:55,071 --> 00:38:57,683
Listen, Hailey...

869
00:38:58,814 --> 00:39:01,034
I don't want you meeting
with IAD right now.

870
00:39:01,077 --> 00:39:06,126
Just tell them--tell them you
need to see your FOP rep first.

871
00:39:07,040 --> 00:39:09,303
- Okay.

872
00:39:23,883 --> 00:39:27,539
- For someone who has had
a long week, you look great.

873
00:39:28,540 --> 00:39:30,019
- And it's only Wednesday.

874
00:39:30,063 --> 00:39:31,804
- [chuckles]

875
00:39:31,847 --> 00:39:34,067
Hmm.

876
00:39:35,285 --> 00:39:36,765
- So, this Halstead thing...

877
00:39:36,809 --> 00:39:39,072
- Oh, don't worry about that.
He's your partner.

878
00:39:39,986 --> 00:39:42,162
I get it.

879
00:39:48,473 --> 00:39:51,214
- I do have to ask, though.

880
00:39:52,085 --> 00:39:54,174
Why didn't you take the shot?

881
00:39:57,699 --> 00:40:00,267
- I don't know.

882
00:40:02,051 --> 00:40:03,836
I just froze.

883
00:40:05,620 --> 00:40:07,970
I got a lot on my mind,
I guess.

884
00:40:08,014 --> 00:40:09,668
- Yeah.

885
00:40:09,711 --> 00:40:12,192
Yeah, I know.
I've noticed.

886
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:15,891
I don't wanna push you.

887
00:40:15,935 --> 00:40:17,458
If you don't want to talk about
it, we don't have to.

888
00:40:17,502 --> 00:40:19,678
But the stories that you told
about your father...

889
00:40:19,721 --> 00:40:22,681
[solemn music]

890
00:40:22,724 --> 00:40:24,683
♪

891
00:40:24,726 --> 00:40:28,338
- Yeah.

892
00:40:28,382 --> 00:40:31,254
Those were true.

893
00:40:35,563 --> 00:40:38,044
He wasn't like that
all the time.

894
00:40:39,393 --> 00:40:41,264
Sometimes he was funny.

895
00:40:41,308 --> 00:40:43,136
And sweet.

896
00:40:44,616 --> 00:40:46,966
It's a lot more complicated
than people think.

897
00:40:55,496 --> 00:40:58,934
- Come over here.

898
00:41:19,477 --> 00:41:19,825
.

899
00:41:19,868 --> 00:41:22,523
[dramatic music]

900
00:41:22,567 --> 00:41:29,791
♪

901
00:41:48,810 --> 00:41:52,031
[wolf howling]

